Package com.commander4j.db

Class JDBPallet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.commander4j.db.JDBPallet
  • public class JDBPallet
extends java.lang.Object
    The JDBPallet is used to insert/update/delete records from the APP_PALLET table. The pallet table is one of the primary tables within the application and has strong ties to the APP_PALLET_HISTORY table. This class contains many helper methods which are used to perform high level transactions. Also a lot of validation is performed by this class.

    See Also:
    JDBPalletHistory

      • confirm

        public java.lang.Boolean confirm()
        This method will confirm an unconfirmed pallet. When a pallet label is printed it's default status is unconfirmed. An unconfirmed pallet won't be interfaced to an external system until it's confirmed. The process of confirming a pallet involves a lot of validation. If the confirmation is successful the method will return True. If the method returns false the reason for the failure can be determined by using the getErrorMessage()
        Returns:
        Indicates of the method completed successfully
        See Also:
        getErrorMessage()
